events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 34 points and Jonas Valanciunas added 27 points and 12 rebounds as the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Washington Wizards 132-112 on Monday night.
— Jayson Tatum scored 32 points and Jaylen Brown added 19 as the Boston Celtics beat the Chicago Bulls 107-99 Monday night and reached the midway point of their season with the NBA's best record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics top Bulls 107-99, improve NBA's best record to 29-12

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo could feel the Bucks playing with more energy and could sense a shift in their confidence on their 3-point shots.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks come from 17 down, stop Knicks' four-game win streak

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones, filling in for Ja Morant, had 24 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 16 and the Memphis Grizzlies withstood a second-half San Antonio rally to beat the Spurs 121-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies withstand late rally to defeat Spurs 121-113

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic needed only five shots on his way to a league-leading 11th triple-double of the season. How's that for efficient.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic lead charge as Nuggets beat Lakers 122-109

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored a season-high 30 points and the Sacramento Kings hit a franchise record 23 3-pointers to beat the Orlando Magic 136-111 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harrison Barnes scores 30, Kings blowout Magic 136-111
